{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"a3d87716-da38-40ce-a2a4-08f7721dcea1","content":"Here are the MSBuild evaluation performance issues in this project:\n\n---\n\n### 1. Recursive wildcard glob — `**\\*.*` (line 9, `.csproj`)\n```xml\n<AdditionalFiles Include=\"**\\*.*\" Exclude=\"**\\bin\\**;**\\obj\\**\" />\n```\nThe `**\\*.*` glob forces MSBuild to enumerate the **entire directory tree** on every evaluation. This is the single most expensive pattern here — it scales with the number of files on disk and cannot be cached across evaluations if any file changes.\n\n**Fix:** Narrow the glob to specific extensions or directories, e.g. `**\\*.txt` or `src\\**\\*.cs`.\n\n---\n\n### 2. File I/O via property function (line 13, `.csproj`)\n```xml\n<BuildNotes>$([System.IO.File]::ReadAllText('build-notes.txt'))</BuildNotes>\n```\nCalling `System.IO.File.ReadAllText` during evaluation performs **disk I/O every time the project is evaluated** (IDE reload, design-time build, every restore). Property functions run synchronously and block the evaluator.\n\n**Fix:** Move this to a target that runs only during build (e.g., inside a `<Target>`) or read the file as a `Content`/`None` item instead.\n\n---\n\n### 3. Three-level deep import chain (`level1 → level2 → level3`)\nEach `<Import>` triggers a new file open + parse + evaluate cycle. While three levels is not catastrophic, deeply chained imports add up because MSBuild must resolve each one sequentially. This also makes the evaluation order harder to reason about.\n\n**Fix:** Flatten into a single `.props` file if the settings are simple enough, or at minimum avoid unnecessary nesting.\n\n---\n\n### Summary (ranked by impact)\n\n| # | Issue | Impact |\n|---|-------|--------|\n| 1 | `**\\*.*` recursive glob | **High** — filesystem walk on every eval |\n| 2 | `File.ReadAllText` in property | **Medium** — synchronous I/O during eval |\n| 3 | Chained `.props` imports | **Low** — adds eval overhead, mostly a maintainability concern |","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"4f84be44-b346-4274-a9d6-05a6be98b71f","outputTokens":534},"id":"431fbcbc-0d1b-4f21-aaea-cf056eded369","timestamp":"2026-04-05T01:07:34.341Z","parentId":"df546e7e-b899-4328-b070-c2a003ffcc83"}
